It's just your average Burger King, which is one of my least favourite fast food franchises. That's in the eye of the beholder, of course. But this location is pretty run down, and last time I was there the floors were so slippery that I feared for my safety. I disabled and so other people might not be as troubled by the slippery floors. But I don't think I would go here when the weather is bad again, if I could help it. It was a much worse problem than other businesses that I have noticed. It felt like I was ice skating just trying to get to the bathroom. I would be really worried for an elderly person or someone with more serious balance issues. On the other hand they are open late and have public bathrooms, as well as cheap food and lots of deals/special offers. And I have always found the workers there to be helpful and kind. In conclusion, just your run of the mill fast food place, and my only real complaint is the slippery floors when it's been raining out.
